          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_AVt4mm": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "The Marinière",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>When it comes to iconic apparel, few items combine timeless style and function like the Marinière. Much like blue jeans, this traditional striped shirt has evolved over the past century, transforming from a practical uniform worn by sailors into an everyday staple for men and women around the world. The Marinière certainly isn’t tied to a particular time of year either - one of the best things about it is its year-round appeal.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "47bfb772-5b4f-4198-802a-23f7ca18048d": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Fit",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>The oversized fit, the<br/>dropped sleeves and wide boat neck are hallmarks of our design. Taken together, they represent a unique, modern and fashionable update of this classic look, making them perfect for every outfit.<br/></p><p>Available from S to L. We recommend ordering your normal size. Consult our sizing chart for the correct measurements. If you prefer a slimmer fit, order a size down. If you are unsure or need some advice, send us a message and we will be happy to help.<br/><br/>The model in the photo is 165 cm tall and wears<br/>size M.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "e9567a30-a8a4-47b3-ac6b-dd845b2d3a7c": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Fabric & Care",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>We produce the marinière in Italy on a manual loom. This means that we do not cut the various parts from ready-made printed fabrics; rather, each sweater is knitted by skilled artisans from more than 2 and a half kilometers of raw yarn.</p><p>To keep your Marinière looking its best, hand wash or machine wash at 30 degrees, then hang to dry. If needed, iron inside out or steam to take out creases.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "d808420e-8e92-4566-9948-7577a69f3f77": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Handmade Embroidery",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>Our Marinières are hand embroidered with needle and thread, making each one unique. </p><p>Each pieces is also hand numbered, from 1 to 99.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_fwJdwf": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Shipping & Returns",
            "icon": "none",
            "content": "<p>Shipping is free.</p><p>Once your Marinière is dispatched, you'll receive an email with tracking details. We ship all over the world. And if you’re based in the EU, we will be sending your items directly from Italy so that you won’t incur additional customs fees.</p><p>If for any reason you wanted to return your Marinière, we accept returns within 14 days of delivery as long as the Marinièere is in perfect condition.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
